Extensive deforestation of cedar trees in South and Central America has led the European Union to consider trade restrictions.
Germany, as the current EU presidency, highlights the vulnerability of the spiny dogfish due to overfishing.
Other species like Brazilian lobsters and sawfish are also at risk.
The UN Environment Programme warns of threats to biodiversity from habitat destruction and climate change.
Conservation efforts are crucial, as highlighted by the protection of coral species under CITES.
The importance of sustainable practices in coral harvesting is emphasized to ensure the survival of marine ecosystems and valuable wildlife commodities.
